## **Key Patterns Summary**

| Aspect | IRC | Nostr |
|--------|-----|-------|
| **Complexity** | Medium | Simple |
| **Chat Types** | `["direct", "group"]` | `["direct"]` (DM-only) |
| **Media** | `true` | `false` |
| **Text Chunk Limit** | 350 chars | 4000 chars |
| **Account Model** | Multi-account capable | Single/default account focus |
| **Gateway Model** | `runStoppablePassiveMonitor()` | Returns `{ stop: () => {...} }` |
| **Directory Support** | Peers + Groups | N/A (DM-only) |
| **Groups Support** | Full: `requireMention`, `toolPolicy` | N/A |
| **Pairing** | Text-based via `sendMessageIrc()` | Text-based via `bus.sendDm()` |
| **Export Pattern** | Core plugin only | Plugin + utilities + HTTP routes |
| **Dependencies** | SDK only | SDK + `nostr-tools` |
| **Config Adapter** | `createScopedChannelConfigAdapter` | `createTopLevelChannelConfigAdapter` |
| **HTTP Routes** | None | Profile endpoints in `registerFull()` |
| **Bus/Runtime** | Provider-managed | Active bus map + metrics caching |

Both plugins use the same foundational pattern of `createChatChannelPlugin()` but diverge significantly based on their feature set—IRC handles the complexity of groups, multi-channel configuration, and media delivery, while Nostr simplifies to DM-only with relay management and profile publishing capabilities.

